Unemployed persons from vulnerable groups face difficulties and obstacles in job search and employment. Local government is facing difficulties in the promotion and implementation of Employment Programmes and Social services that meet the needs of vulnerable groups.
- In 2015, 318 hard-to-employ people got 6-month short-term employment in 38 municipalities. The total number of short-term employments created in the period from 2012 to 2015 is 538. In average, 70% of them are women and app. 40% are youth (aged up to 29 years);
- In the period 2014- 2015, 1,819 Roma unemployed from 12 municipalities were supported by employment coaches and mentors with up-to-date information about the employment opportunities available in the country.

